{
  "project_extract.notes_title": "Notes",
  "project_extract.article": "The «Text extraction» section controls how document content is obtained.\n\nA key difficulty with many formats is that it is unclear what is on images: it may be a text scan, a photo, or a diagram.\n\nMost settings relate to image handling; if you prefer not to tune everything, the defaults work for many cases.\n\nThings to watch:\n- PDF render scale and image size limits (office documents, standalone images, including SVG after rasterization) strongly affect cost and recognition time; values much above ~1500 px are rarely worth it\n- If your PDFs are scans, they often have both an image layer and a low-quality OCR text layer; adaptive mode or full-page render is usually better\n- If office documents truly have no images, choose an algorithm that ignores images to save processing",
